methods.cpuProfilingAvailable:
Check if CPU profiling (e.g. ThreadProfiler.getCurrentThreadCpuTime() and ThreadProfiler.getCurrentThreadUserTime()) is
 available (supported and enabled).

:return: (boolean) Whether CPU profiling is available.
methods.getCurrentThreadAllocatedBytes:
Get the approximate number of total bytes allocated by the current thread.

:return: (long) The approximate number of total bytes allocated by the current thread, or
         QueryConstants.NULL_LONG if unavailable.
methods.getCurrentThreadCpuTime:
Get the approximate number of total nanoseconds the current thread has executed (in system or user mode) since
 CPU time measurement started.

:return: (long) The approximate number of total nanoseconds the current thread has executed, or
         QueryConstants.NULL_LONG if unavailable.
methods.getCurrentThreadUserTime:
Get the approximate number of total nanoseconds the current thread has executed (in user mode) since CPU time
 measurement started.

:return: (long) The approximate number of total nanoseconds the current thread has executed in user mode, or
         QueryConstants.NULL_LONG if unavailable.
methods.memoryProfilingAvailable:
Check if memory profiling (e.g. ThreadProfiler.getCurrentThreadAllocatedBytes()) is available (supported and enabled).

:return: (boolean) Whether memory profiling is available.

text: The "null" ThreadProfiler implementation, which supports no actual measurements.
